Interface DoublyLinkedList<T extends DoublyLinkedList.Item<?>>

All Known Implementing Classes:

public interface DoublyLinkedList<T extends DoublyLinkedList.Item<?>>
extends Iterable<T>

Framework for managing a doubly linked list. The purpose of DoublyLinkedList is simply and solely so that we can override the entries with our own classes. This makes removal for example extremely fast: O(1) not O(n). In any other case we can use LinkedList.

Author:
tavin
